SonarQube is a code quality checking tool used in DevOps.
It is developed using Java and supports more than 30 programming languages.
We use SonarQube to review code and find mistakes in the project.
It generates a code review report which is shared with the development team.
Code review is part of the build process.
DevOps team runs SonarQube analysis.
Development team fixes the issues found in the report.

---

# Types of Issues in SonarQube

SonarQube detects the following issues:

- Bugs → These are dangerous and can break the application
- Vulnerabilities → These are security issues in the code
- Code Smells → These are bad coding practices (not critical but should be improved)
- Duplicate Code → Same code written multiple times
- Code Coverage → Shows how much code is tested

---

# Quality Profile

Quality Profile is a set of rules used to check code quality.
Each programming language has its own quality profile.

Examples:
- Java Project → Java Quality Profile
- Python Project → Python Quality Profile
- PHP Project → PHP Quality Profile

We can create our own custom quality profile.
We can also set a profile as default for all projects.
We can assign a specific profile to a specific project.

Example:
Name: SBI_Project_QP  
Language: Java  
Parent: None  

---

# Quality Gate

Quality Gate tells whether the project code quality is passed or failed.
If Quality Gate is failed, we should NOT deploy the code.
SonarQube provides a default quality gate.
We can also create a custom quality gate.

